8 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
9 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 2667 of Title 63, unless there
10 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
11 As used in this act:
12 1. "Commissioner" means the Oklahoma Commissioner of Health;
13 2. "Department" means the State Department of Health;
14 3. "Emergency care" means health care services provided to
15 achieve stabilization as needed for conditions that reasonably
16 appear to constitute a life- or limb-threatening emergency based on
17 the presenting symptoms of the patient;
18 4. "Facility" means a short-term emergency and nonemergency
19 hybrid medical facility;
20 5. "Maximum emergency stay period" means any patient who is
21 treated for an emergency situation and is prohibited from being
22 treated or held any longer than twenty-four (24) hours so long as
23 the necessary treatment required is deemed an emergency. Maximum
24 emergency stay period shall not apply to patients that are
HB1630 HFLR Page 2
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.
1 stab ilized and needing further treatment from being provided
2 nonemergency care;
3 6. "Nonemergency care" means all health care that is not for
4 life-threatening conditions or covered as emergency care under an
5 existing health care policy, including, but not limited to, the
6 following services:
7 a. diagnostic testing,
8 b. lab testing,
9 c. outpatient services,
10 d. primary care, and
11 e. X-rays, magnetic resonance imaging (MRI), and other
12 types of imaging; and
13 7. "Short-term emergency and nonemergency hybrid medical
14 facility" means a dual-sided facility, structurally separate and
15 distinct from a hospital that is open twenty-four (24) hours per day
16 and seven (7) days a week, with one side of the facility providing
17 emergency care and the other side of the facility providing
18 nonemergency care.
